{
  "answer": "**Elene** by Cynewulf (an Old English verse poem), Chapter 1.[^1]\n\nThe named tribes appear in the opening narration of Emperor Constantine encamped by the Danube: \"The Hunnish people and Hrethgoths hardened, Franks and Hugas, a fearsome force,\"[^2] gathered on the far bank against him.\n\nLater in the same chapter, a heavenly herald shows Constantine the gem-adorned cross in a dream, inscribed with \"letters of light\": \"the victory-tree, with words woven on it, shining and splendid: “By this sign, conquer.\"[^3]\n\n[^1]: Cynewulf, *Elene*, Chapter 1, [/works/cynewulf-elene-d2d132/01/translation/](https://falsafa.corpus/works/cynewulf-elene-d2d132/01/translation/).\n\n[^2]: Cynewulf, *Elene*, [paragraph](/works/cynewulf-elene-d2d132/01/translation/#p-14a3be).\n\n[^3]: Cynewulf, *Elene*, [paragraph](/works/cynewulf-elene-d2d132/01/translation/#p-306e06).",
